DOC.HEADLINE: BRIEFLY : BANKING & FINANCE
DOC.TEXT: Treasury_Note Yields Rise : Yields on two-year notes rose in auction to the highest level in more_than three years.The high yield was 6.88 % , up from 6.55 % at the last auction Sept . 27 . It was the highest rate since two-year notes sold for 6.94 % on July 23 , 1991 . The notes will carry a coupon interest_rate of 6.875 % , with each $ 10 # 000 in face_value selling for $ 9 # 999.10 .
